      <p><span class="Section-Header">Statement About Drinking Water</span></p> 
      <p> </p> 
      <p>The Gray Charter School is not affected by the recent concerns regarding elevated amounts of lead that was discovered in some of the city’s water supplies. The State Department of Education understands that lead in drinking water continues to be an issue within local school communities and has worked in collaboration with the State Department of Health and the Department of Environmental Protection, to create a back-to-school package of <a target="_blank" href="forms/Resources_for_School_Districts_on_Testing_for_Lead_in_Drinking_Water.8.19.pdf">resources</a> for school districts to use regarding testing for lead in school drinking water and educating families on prevention, screening, and intervention related to lead exposure.</p> 
