      <p><span class="Section-Header">GCS receives NATIONAL AWARD!</span></p> 
      <p> </p> 
      <p align="center"><a target="_blank" href="http://www2.ed.gov/programs/nclbbrs/index.html"><img alt="BRS" height="151" longdesc="images/Eagle-CMYK-2010-r.jpg" width="151" src="images/Eagle-CMYK-2010-r.jpg"></a></p> 
      <p> </p> 
      <p>On Thursday, September 9, 2010, U.S. Secretary of Education Arne Duncan recognized The Gray Charter School, one of only 304 schools, as a 2010 National Blue Ribbon School. The honor -- alongside those of eight other New Jersey schools, two of them private -- was officially recognized at an awards ceremony Nov. 15-16 in Washington, D.C.</p> 
      <p> </p> 
      <p>Read the entire news story on <a target="_blank" href="http://www.njspotlight.com/stories/10/0909/2038/">NJ Spotlight.com</a>!</p> 
      <p> </p> 
      <p>View the <a target="_blank" href="news/BRS_GCS_2010.pdf">PRESS RELEASE</a> and detailed information about what it takes to be recognized as a National Blue Ribbon School.</p> 
